  "description": "Nucleosynthesis is the formation of atomic nuclei. Big Bang nucleosynthesis (BBN) refers specifically to the formation of light elements -- hydrogen, helium, and trace amounts of lithium and deuterium -- in the first few minutes after the [Big Bang](./big-bang.md), when the entire universe was hot and dense enough for nuclear fusion.",
